cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.SI

The paper discusses the use of machine learning and artificial intelligence in analyzing language and identifying biases. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses statistical machine learning models, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the implications of their findings for AI and machine learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also touches on the fields of psychology and sociology, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), respectively.
